Activist Boniface Mwangi launched his first ever book at the Alliance Francaise, Nairobi, on Saturday evening. Unbounded takes readers through the activist s journey from his passion for activism as far as human rights are concerned.An exhibition of his selected works was also up for sale. Mwangi s best works includes the images taken during the post-election violence in 2007-08.The launch was attended by a diverse range of guests, among them State House head of digital content Dennis Itumbi and fellow activist Houghton Irungu.Also present were Christian in Politics founder Dennis Nthumbi and Kenya Copyright Board director David Muriithi.